div.p:
This Court is Superiour to the other Tribunals, that ſo the rigour of the Law in them might be here moderated, and amended according to Conſcience and Equity; and proceeding by Engliſh Bill, the Witneſſes are examined in private; the Decrees in Engliſh or Latin; no Jury, but all Sentences given by the Judge of the Court, much like to the Courts of the Civil Law; 
                              ••

                           binds the perſon only, and not his Lands or Goods.
